    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean you're saying it's a \"challenge\" and a \"fine line,\" but it sounds like you're leaning pretty hard towards the government side. if a religious organization's whole identity is built on these values, isn't forcing them to comply just a form of state-sponsored intolerance? shouldn't the state be neutral enough to let them live their lives without interference, even if it's not perfectly \"uniform\"? why does the secular state's need for uniformity always seem to trump the actual freedom of the individual or the group?",
